<div class=Section1>
<p>
<h1 align=center style='margin-left:0in;text-align:center;text-indent:0in'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Symbol;font-weight:normal'>+</span><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Verdana","sans-serif"'>What has Orthodox
Christian Ministry meant to me?</span> </h1>

<p>
<h1 align=center style='margin-left:0in;text-align:center;text-indent:0in'><span
style='font-size:12.5pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black;font-weight:normal'>+</span><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Verdana","sans-serif"'>A letter from an
inmate</span></h1>

<p>
<h3 align=center style='margin-left:0in;text-align:center;text-indent:0in'><span
style='font-size:12.5pt;font-family:"Helvetica Neue";color:black'>Nov 24, 2015</span></h3>

<p>
<p class=MsoBodyText align=center style='text-align:center'><b><span
style='font-size:12.5pt;font-family:"Helvetica Neue";color:black'>&nbsp;</span></b></p>
<div>

<p>
<table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 hspace=0 vspace=0 align=center>
 <tr>
  <td valign=top align=left style='padding-top:0in;padding-right:0in;
  padding-bottom:0in;padding-left:0in'>
  <p class=MsoNormal><img width=366 height=351 id="Patriarch Joseph the All-Comely"
  src="https://www.orthodox.net//ikons/patriarch-joseph-the-all-comely.png"></p>  </td>
 </tr>
</table>

<p>
</div>

<p>
<br clear=ALL>

<p>
<p class=MsoBodyText align=center style='text-align:center'><b><span
style='font-size:12.5pt;font-family:"Helvetica Neue";color:black'>St Joseph the
All Comely Texas Prison Ministry</span></b></p>
<p class=MsoBodyText align=center style='text-align:center'><b><span
style='font-size:12.5pt;font-family:"Helvetica Neue";color:black'>We turn
Eeyores into Tiggers! </span></b></p>
<h3 style='margin-left:0in;text-indent:0in'><span style='font-size:12.5pt;
font-family:"Helvetica Neue";color:black'>Introduction</span></h3>

<p>
<p class=MsoBodyText><span style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>I
am speaking soon at an Orthodox youth conference (</span><span
class=MsoHyperlink><span style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>St
Herman's Youth Conference, Dec 28-Jan 1</span></span><span style='font-family:
"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>)<a href="#_edn1" name="_ednref1" title=""><span
class=MsoEndnoteReference><span class=MsoEndnoteReference><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>[i]</span></span></span></a>
- on Prison Ministry, and I asked the men I see to tell me something about how
our humble ministry has affected them. I intend to read some of theirб
responses to the youth. I was, as the Fathers no doubt never said ,цblown awayц
by this letter. This person, whom I know very well, has gone through many
positive changes, and I joke with him that he was gone from a cynical фEeyoreц
to at least half of a фTiggerц. I am not telling tales out of school here,
because he is happy to tell anyone who will listen how his attitude has
changed. </span></p>
<p class=MsoBodyText><span style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>I
sometimes have attitude problems too. I get tired of the grind of prison
ministry, and sometimes wonder if I am making much difference. Of course, this
is just a фstupid human trickц. I keep on getting up at 3am on Wednesdays and
rolling down the highway, but I am not always a фTiggerц about it. Letters like
this help me immensely. </span></p>
<p class=MsoBodyText><span style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>I
thought I would share it with you, since he knows it will be made public, and
to encourage you, and (full disclosure) to encourage everyone to consider
donating to our ministry, which costs about a thousand dollars a month in
travel, books, and postage. We recently bought $750.00 worth of books and
prayer ropes for the inmates. If you want to help our ongoing needs, or give
any donation, please contact me at (Priest seraphim), <a
href="mailto:seraphim@orthodox.net">mailto:seraphim@orthodox.net</a>. An always
out of date description of our fast changing ministry (with a Pay Pal donate
button) is at: </span><span class=MsoHyperlink><span style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";
color:black'><a
href="https://www.orthodox.net//ministries/orthodox-prison-ministry.html">https://www.orthodox.net//ministries/orthodox-prison-ministry.html</a></span></span></p>
<p class=MsoBodyText align=center style='text-align:center'><span
style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>-----------------------</span></p>
<p class=MsoBodyText><b><span style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";
color:black'>Re: thankfulness</span></b><span style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";
color:black'> </span></p>
<p class=MsoBodyText><span style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>Thank
you again for your tireless love and devotion for all of us who are
incarcerated. </span></p>
<p class=MsoBodyText><span style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class=MsoBodyText><span style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>Seldom
do I feel the true love of our God in this place, so it is such a joy to know I
am loved when I am at the Orthodox services. Although I'm not Orthodox, I enjoy
your service more than any other because God is real to me when I am there. You
ask us today to write how Orthodox service has affected us individually so that
you can share it with your prison ministry youth talk. This is weighed heavily
on me since you left, because of the importance. </span></p>
<p class=MsoBodyText><span style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class=MsoBodyText><span style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>First
and foremost, I expect others will say that the youth should learn from their
past mistakes because this is not a place to spend their lives. I will not. I
was one of those youth who was told by many others to not follow in their
footsteps and this caused me to go down paths that I had to travel to become
who I am today. I am NOT saying to ignore good advice, but we all have to
choose our paths in life. It is the outcome of those choices that determines
our destiny. </span></p>
<p class=MsoBodyText><span style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class=MsoBodyText><span style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>For
me, my destiny was to come here prison so that I could see the love of God. My
whole life I could not feel or understand what love was. I rarely felt I was
loved by my parents, so I thought to gain attention from anyone, usually in a
negative way. Coming in and out of prisons across the country (One state,
another state, and now Texas) was the result of my acting out. </span></p>
<p class=MsoBodyText><span style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class=MsoBodyText><span style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>I
am now 50(something) years old with no children. I have felt for years that I
would die alone and that was the end of things. Today, although I still
struggle with everyday things in life, I know that I am loved by God. I am NOT
alone. I sought Him out. He has always been there. Some say that my life is
hopeless. I have said it for years. So be it. I have made the choices in life
and now face the consequences of those choices. The difference now is that I
know I am loved and God is never going to leave me alone. Because I finally
realize this, I surround myself with those who God sends my way for comfort. </span></p>
<p class=MsoBodyText><span style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class=MsoBodyText><span style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>It
is for this reason and many others, that I continue to attend the Orthodox
service. I see God in everything that you say and do and I can now see that God
has wanted me for what God has wanted for me my whole life. PEACE. Thank you
for always being you, and sharing the love of God constantly in both word
indeed. </span></p>
<p class=MsoBodyText><span style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class=MsoBodyText><span style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>May
God's will be done through our humble prayers always. </span></p>
<p class=MsoBodyText><span style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class=MsoBodyText><span style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>In
his perfect love, N</span></p>
<p class=MsoBodyText><span style='font-size:7.5pt;font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";
color:black'>&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class=MsoBodyText><span class=MsoHyperlink><span style='font-size:8.0pt;
font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'><a
href="https://www.orthodox.net//full-voice/prison-ministry-visits_2015-12-04-letter-from-inmate+how-has-orthodox-prison-ministry-affected-me.doc">https://www.orthodox.net//full-voice/prison-ministry-visits_2015-12-04-letter-from-inmate+how-has-orthodox-prison-ministry-affected-me.doc</a></span></span></p>
<p class=MsoBodyText><span class=MsoHyperlink><span style='font-size:8.0pt;
font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'><a
href="https://www.orthodox.net//full-voice/prison-ministry-visits_2015-12-04-letter-from-inmate+how-has-orthodox-prison-ministry-affected-me.pdf">https://www.orthodox.net//full-voice/prison-ministry-visits_2015-12-04-letter-from-inmate+how-has-orthodox-prison-ministry-affected-me.pdf</a></span></span></p>
<p class=MsoBodyText><br>
<br>
</p>
</div>

<p>
<div><br clear=all>

<p>
<hr align=left size=1 width="33%">

<p>
<div id=edn1>

<p>
<p class=MsoEndnoteText><a href="#_ednref1" name="_edn1" title=""><span
class=EndnoteCharacters><span style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"'><span
class=EndnoteCharacters><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"'>[i]</span></span></span></span></a>бббб Info
about the St Herman's Youth Conference, 2015 (in McKinney, TX) <a
href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1__AYJUJNwhWjVlfo-MHt0o940VzCrJ8YWACYQvRvZxM/viewform?c=0&amp;w=1">https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1__AYJUJNwhWjVlfo-MHt0o940VzCrJ8YWACYQvRvZxM/viewform?c=0&amp;w=1</a></p>
</div>

<p>
</div>

